<div type="definition">
<p>RUB AND SMEAR USING LIQUID so as to CAUSE TO BECOME SMOOTH AND SHINING.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Zhuó 琢 refers primarily to the polishing of jade.</p>
<p>2. Cuō 磋 is to transform a rude product by polishing it.</p>
<p>3. Dǐ 砥 refers to sharpening of an artefact with the small and fine whetstone.</p>
<p>4. Lì 礪 refers to sharpening of an artefact with the crude brushing stone.</p>
        </div>
